                        "name": "Matt Spinler",
                        "email": "spinler@us.ibm.com",
                        "username": "spinler"
                    },
                    "message": "nice! After all these years I just thought it was working as designed and so I would do the argN stuff myself, after forgetting about it and seeing things not work."
                },
                {
                    "file": "include/sdbusplus/bus/match.hpp",
                    "line": 142,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Lei YU",
                        "email": "mine260309@gmail.com",
                        "username": "mine260309"
                    },
                    "message": "This changes the API's behavior, and there are several users of this API, e.g.\n\nhttps://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-user-manager/blob/90b84ad9d6cfe44daae2d9cfbbdb9bd616e4c814/phosphor-ldap-config/ldap_config.cpp#L66\nhttps://github.com/openbmc/pldm/blob/58cbcaf2103f9a6d8f218121c38d1f82133c2e25/requester/mctp_endpoint_discovery.cpp#L19\n\nProbably you need to make sure the behavior is not impacted."
                },
                {
                    "file": "include/sdbusplus/bus/match.hpp",
                    "line": 142,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Andrew Jeffery",
                        "email": "andrew@codeconstruct.com.au",
                        "username": "amboar"
                    },
                    "message": "I'd like to ask the reverse question: Were those code-paths properly exercised in testing?"
                },
                {
                    "file": "include/sdbusplus/bus/match.hpp",
                    "line": 142,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "Looking again at it, it looks like the ObjectManager is who emits the signal, so a path match would be on the ObjectManager path. Since OMs are rarely at a specific required position in the tree, I suspect most of these current matches are \"wrong\" from a \"right way to do dbus\" perspective but might actually have worked due to tight coupling with a particular implementation. \n\nWe will need to audit all uses before I merge this, even though I suspect that this change is probably the more useful implementation."
                },
                {
                    "file": "include/sdbusplus/bus/match.hpp",
                    "line": 142,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "I looked through all the instances of `interfacesAdded` I could find (not `interfacesRemoved`).  There are at least 8 cpp parts that are calling this function.  I suspect many of these aren't working as the author intended, but we can't just blindly change the implementation of this function.\n\nThere are 13 files already doing `interfaceAdded() + argNpath(...)` on their own.\n\nThere are 5 files already doing `interfaceAdded() + path(...)` on their own and these are likely also not correct.\n\nIn light of this my suggestion would be that we:\n\n1. Add interfacesAddedAtPath() with this argNpath behavior.\n2. Remove interfaceAdded(p) and fix all the resulting compile failures to use `interfaceAdded() + path(...)` (as a separate commit from #1).\n3. Revisit all instances of `interfacesAdded` and fix anyone using `+ path(...)` to use a valid version of `interfacesAddedAtPath`.\n4. In a few months consider renaming interfacesAddedAtPath back to interfacesAdded (probably with a using-alias so we can keep AtPath for a period of time to fix them all up)."
                },
                {
                    "file": "include/sdbusplus/bus/match.hpp",
                    "line": 142,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Andrew Jeffery",
                        "email": "andrew@codeconstruct.com.au",
                        "username": "amboar"
                    },
                    "message": "I'll rework the patch for 1 and we can start poking at 2."
                },
                {
                    "file": "include/sdbusplus/bus/match.hpp",
                    "line": 142,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Andrew Jeffery",
                        "email": "andrew@codeconstruct.com.au",
                        "username": "amboar"
                    },
                    "message": "Done"
                }
            ],
